    <item>
      <title>Proposal for Mitigation Changes</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=24266#M24266</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I am of the opinion that the triviality of content in conjunction with the ease of high stat gear acquisition in the game has resulting in a blurring of class-based advantages that needs to be addressed in a way that does not unduly impact players and the classes they play.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A) Class Based Mitigation and Gear&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*Irrespective of level of gear, there should be a clear distinction in the mitigation of incoming dps from a mob between classes/archetypes via the DI distribution at any particular interaction of player AC and mob ATK.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*As has been stated by various devs, and as is the COMMON perceptions of what the roles of the various classes should be (class mavens notwithstanding) the mitigation of incoming dps by player classes should be WAR &amp;gt;PAL/SK &amp;gt; OTHER (I am purposefully limiting this to the actual heavy tank archetypes, arguments of where the rest belong is a different issue, the point being that knights should mitigate dps better than other classes and warriors should mitigate better than knights).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*DI(-1) was introduced to warriors as a method of keeping the gap between warriors and knights, but with the exponential rise in player AC since that time, and the relative stagnation of the content with regard to interaction with player AC to create DI distributions, this mitigation advantage has become smaller in real world content.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*I propose two changes to revitalize the tanking gaps between warriors and knights and knights and others:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) Move warriors to DI(-3)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) Move knights to DI(-1)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3) Change the warrior worn AC modifier from ~1.57 to ~1.65 (this will result in around 100-200 ac boost to warriors depending on where their gear is)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*The DI mod change is self-explanatory, it creates an always on, class-based rather than gear-based tanking disparity between classes and archetypes, and in conjunction with higher player AC more accurately results in mitigation differences that mirror where things were when DI(-1) went in.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*The AC modifier is a way to get around the problem of gear that is more and more often lacking in class specific armor sets, thus negating one of the advantages warriors were supposed to have, and is also a nod to the realities of warrior gear choices in that warriors are more likely to wear HP based augs over AC based augs due to their raid role as an MT that needs to maintain enough hps for a heal chain to keep them up while under defensive disciplines. It also just makes plain sense for the same reason that warriors get a greater stamina to hp conversion rate.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*Avoidance is ignored in this argument because it has relatively little differential effect on war vs knight balance, and is more of a plate tank versus light tank balancing issue.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;B) Viability of Shield Use and Stats&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*When it comes to weapon choice and setups, it is all about dps. Either the dps you can output or the dps you have coming into you. The stat disparity between mainhand and offhand setups versus 2h setups is pointless and results in more magelo-fluffing and knights using 1h/shield in situations that its pointless to do so rather than any balance issue. The difference in stats between dualwield or 1h/shield and a 2her used to be small (10-20%) and has not grown to the nearly 75% range in many cases.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*2h stats (ac and hp specifically) should be on par or slightly under than which you get from a mainhand and offhand item for several reasons:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) There is very little point in a warrior to ever use a 2her outside of using something like fellstrike discipline, when they can get a dual wield set up that provides equivalent dps while providing far more stats.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) With regard to plate tanks, the use of a 1h/shield and the over-cap ac and shield block avoidance creates MORE than enough benefit to use over a 2her, the stat differences are overkill.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3) The basic statistic inferiority of 2hers is enough in and of itself (fewer procs, meaning less dps that scales with things like crit aa, almost always less mods like shielding and avoidance, the reduction in the potential number of focus-like effects, etc), with the hp/ac inferiority being overkill&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;4) The fact that 2hers are the first things to rot in raiding guilds should be reality enough.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*I believe that such a change would result in far more 2h use, which would come closer to that which it seems that some devs somewhere must want with all the 2hers they keep itemizing.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*Due to the impact of shield block on avoidance, shield use needs to be made viable for warriors as it is for knights. In order to do so, there needs to be two changes:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) Aggro generation needs to be changed for warriors, either providing more on-demand aggro or providing shield use specific aggro. Aggro generation does not need to be equivalent to dual wield, but does need to be viable. Enabling procs from bashes and putting anger and eb type effects on shields and augs that go on shields could do it. Maybe a modification to generated aggro (innate echo of anger type thing that stacks with EoA effects) when wielding a shield.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) DPS loss needs to be equivalent to knight dps loss when going to 1h/shield (around 20% rather than 40% like it is for warriors now), either by shield mate weapons *that are itemized with the recognition that warrior aa and skill caps may require lower ratios than knights get* or some mechanic that alters the ratio of mainhand weapon when a warrior wears a shield.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*We all know the issues with shields, and bar a few people that seem to not want warriors to be able to use them, the majority of posters sure seem to be willing to grant the need that this needs to be fixed.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;C) Endurance Regen and Costs and Combat Skill Refresh Times&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*Mostly self-explanatory, there needs to be either an increase in endurance regen and/or a reduction in endurance costs. Warriors should not go OoE anymore often than knights go OoM in groups when we are using these reserves to do little more than maintain aggro over dps classes.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;*Some of these refresh timers need to be looked at, there should be a cost balance that limits the aggro that can be built and maintained by warriors, but the double whammy of high cost and long refresh is unfair. There should be the option of in an "oh crap" moment, lay on the aggro and get it at a costly endurance&amp;nbsp;expense. Maybe a new ability on a different timer that has&amp;nbsp;a VERY high cost that can basically at best be used once in a great while, but which is unlinked from the other disciplines? Hell, if you have to link it with defensive so that it can't be used on raid bosses as a regular method of gaining aggro and tank switches? I don't know.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;------------&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;To me, those changes would balance the tank classes nicely (IMHO). Obviously, I have a different opinion than others. But that's what this knight thinks.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
