      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I still say it's more an issue of raiders and casuals, I have had up to twice the hps of casual tanks in groups and more mana than the casual cleric. You can't balance them against me and hope to be fair. You can't lock casuals out of group zones, the gear mobs drop in those zones should allow a casual tank to upgrade so they can tank there. The raider can't be upgraded by any thing in a group really and has no trouble tanking anywhere, knight or warrior.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I understand that pop had a decent progression tree, but as they add each new exspansion that disparity between casuals and raiders gets bigger and balance for groups becomes more difficult. In fact I have softened some of my stance about "warriors vs knights" because&amp;nbsp;I do see it as more a fairness isuue between high end raiders and casuals. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Casual groups do have encounters where a warrior would be better for then tanking than a knight....as long as they are all causual...If I'm in the group,&amp;nbsp;I&amp;nbsp;end up tanking because I'm the 800 pound gorilla with &amp;nbsp;much better gear, shielding, avoidance, improved 3's on everything and yadda yadda. I admit that allowing raid gear to get so massive is what lead to this, and it is a beast of thier own creation, but It won't wrk to have raid mobs drop wimpier stuff than what we have now.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;They painted themselves into a corner and&amp;nbsp;I don't see an easy way to make it fair and balanced in group formats for casuals that will be any threat to a group of high end raiders. I mean they could&amp;nbsp;I suppose try to make really challangeing zones, but would the gear droped be higher end upgrades? &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Raiders are just going to have to except the fact that they are too uber for most those zones and that raids are thier challange now. Groups are just xp grinds for aa's. if so would you force casuals to have to raid to be able to achieve the high end group format? Every one talks about "price you pay" for chooseing a class,&amp;nbsp;I would offer that thier is a "price to be paid" for being a high end raider, and that's ho hum groups.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
